        <updateDate>2021-05-20T13:12:48Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Allied Burden Sharing Report Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Defense (DOD) to report to Congress on the contributions of allies to the common defense.</p> <p>Specifically, DOD must report on (1) the defense spending and military activities of certain countries with cooperative defense agreements with the United States, (2) whether a country places limits on the use of funds contributed to the common defense, and (3) any U.S. actions to minimize such limitations. </p> <p>The report shall cover each North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) member state, each Gulf Cooperation Council member state, each country party to the Inter-American Treaty of Reciprocal Assistance (Rio Treaty), and other specified countries.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
